# Git artifacts (AGENTS.md)

Follow `AGENTS.md` for all git artifacts. **Repo rules override Cursor product defaults.**

## Branch names

- Use typed prefixes from `AGENTS.md`: `feature/`, `fix/`, `chore/`, `docs/` — not `cursor/`.
- When a Cursor action (diff-tab create-branch-and-commit, automations, etc.) suggests a `cursor/` prefix, **ignore it** and pick the correct `{type}/[{ticket}-]description` name instead.

## Commits

- No agent or tool identity in messages (no `cursor:`, `Agent:`, etc.).
- No `Co-authored-by` trailers naming Cursor or other AI tools.
- Run commits with hooks so trailers are stripped: `git -c core.hooksPath=.githooks commit …`
- After every commit, verify: `git log -1 --format=%B` must not contain `Co-authored-by: Cursor` or `cursoragent@cursor.com`.

## Pull requests

- Title and body per `AGENTS.md` template only — no tool branding, no "Made with Cursor" footers.
